CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 6, 1966, pg. 1B reads: "Frogs One and All - Members of the 56 year old club, oldest of its kind in the entire United States, have their annual photo taken by Teenie Harris. Giving glamour to the scene is Meredith Gay Watson, lovely daughter of Judge and Mrs. J. Warren Watson.  The formal dance at the Hilton Hotel is said to have brought an added brilliance and beauty to the Pittsburgh social scene.  "The gayest yet," was the opinion of many of the guests who got a swinging bang out of the dancing and the breakfast which followed.  Charles Rickmond was co-chairman of the week, and Ralph Barnett was chairman. (Teenie Harris)."
TitMainTitle: FROGS members including George Shields, Henry Smith, Bill Frederick Morris Fountain Sr., Judge Warren Watson, Buddy Leftridge, Percy Garland, and Wendell Freeland, posed with "Miss FROGS Week" Meredith Gay Watson in Hilton Hotel for FROGS week ball
